comments: Maxey (PHI) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Horford (BOS) and Embiid (PHI) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Brogdon (BOS) moves alongside Harden's (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) places his hands against Tatum's (BOS) body and immediately slides his hands off as they disengage.
Tatum (BOS) briefly grasps Maxey's (PHI) jersey off-ball and marginal contact occurs as he slides his hand off to gather the entry pass.
Tucker (PHI) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Embiid (PHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Tucker (PHI) contests Smart's (BOS) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Tatum (BOS) places his hand to Harris' (PHI) front and marginal contact occurs at the start of Harris' drive.
Horford (BOS) places his forearm to Embiid's (PHI) front during his spin move and marginal contact occurs as Embiid releases his pass attempt.
Tucker (PHI) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Harris (PHI) slightly extends his leg out as part of his natural shooting motion and marginal contact occurs with Tatum (BOS) as he contest the jump shot attempt.
Brogdon (BOS) initiates contact with Tucker's (PHI) arm, defending his layup attempt.
Tucker (PHI) briefly grasps Smart's (BOS) arm as he defends over the screen before correcting.
Tucker (PHI) immediately slides his hand off of Brown's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs during the screen.
While defending the screen, Tucker (PHI) makes contact with Smart (BOS), affecting his FOM.
Maxey (PHI) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path, firming up and marginal contact occurs as they move together towards the rim.
Smart (BOS) is moving alongside Embiid's (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during Embiid's drive.
Horford (BOS) makes contact with the ball during Embiid's (PHI) shooting motion and maintains legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs defending his layup attempt.

Play is stopped to determine if Embiid's (PHI) shot attempt made contact with the rim. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined the ball did touch the rim. Since Philadelphia had possession at the time of the whistle, play resumes with Philadelphia retaining possession.
Maxey (PHI) already in Brown's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs to Brown's side as they disengage.
Maxey (PHI) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in Brogdon's (BOS) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Harden (PHI) briefly grasps Horford's (BOS) jersey and releases away as they separate during his drive.
Horford (BOS) arm already extended as he places a resting hand to Harden's (PHI) side and marginal body contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Tatum (BOS) places a collapsing arm to Maxey's (PHI) front during the pick and marginal contact occurs as they come together off ball.
Maxey (PHI) places his hands to Tatum's (BOS) side and immediately slides his hands off moving along his path during his drive.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in White's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs with White's body as he defends over the pick.
Smart (BOS) is in the paint for at or about three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.

Replay review of the offensive foul called on Embiid (PHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Smart (BOS) was outside the restricted area and in a legal guarding position in Embiid's (PHI) path before Embiid started his upward motion to attempt the field goal.
Horford (BOS) establishes himself in Harris' (PHI) path and is firming up as marginal contact occurs to his side.
Brown (BOS) gathers the ball on his left foot and establishes his right foot as his pivot prior to the pass.
Harris (PHI) brings his arm toward Tatum's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs during Tatum's drive.
Harden (PHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
White (BOS) and Harden (PHI) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Harden (PHI) engages with White (BOS) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Harden (PHI) releases away to retrieve the pass.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in White's (BOS) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Horford (BOS) places his forearm to Embiid's (PHI) front as they come together and marginal contact occurs during Embiid's drive.
Brown (BOS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Horford (BOS) initiates contact with Embiid (PHI), affecting his ability to pursue the rebound.
Embiid (PHI) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs to Brown's side as they disengage.
Horford (BOS) extends his leg in Embiid's (PHI) path and affects his SQBR.
White (BOS) brings his hands toward Harris (PHI) and marginal contact occurs as White releases away to roll.
Tatum (BOS) and Maxey (PHI) come together and Tatum goes to, not through, Maxey's space as he releases away from the contact at the start of the drive.
Embiid (PHI) is in the paint for at or about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Maxey (PHI) closes out and makes marginal contact with Tatum (BOS) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Brown (BOS) is moving alongside Harden's (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during his drive.
White (BOS) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly given to PHI.
Tatum (BOS) moves along Embiid's (PHI) path and absorbs the marginal contact while defending his post move in the lane.
There is no clear or conclusive angle that determines if Harden (PHI) steps out of bounds as he gathers the pass.
Maxey (PHI) places his hand to White's (BOS) backside and slides his hand off as marginal contact occurs during the pick.
White (BOS) establishes himself in Harris's (PHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Maxey (PHI) brings his arm toward Tatum's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs during Tatum's drive.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was confirmed to overturn the on-court ruling to a no basket.
